  "prompt": "What are some really good Korean spas in Minneapolis?",
  "response": "Minneapolis has a few highly-regarded Korean spas where you can relax and rejuvenate. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **King Spa & Sauna**:\n   - **Location**: 288 S 2nd Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55401\n   - **Description**: King Spa & Sauna is one of the most popular Korean spas in the area. It features nine distinct sauna rooms, each with unique health benefits, along with traditional Korean body scrubs, massages, and a full-service restaurant serving Korean cuisine. It's open 24 hours, making it convenient for all schedules.\n\n2. **Spa Sota**:\n   - **Location**: 3501 Minnesota Dr, Bloomington, MN 55435 (just outside Minneapolis)\n   - **Description**: While not exclusively a Korean spa, Spa Sota offers a variety of services that align with the Korean spa experience, including body scrubs and massages. The facility is known for its tranquil atmosphere and high-quality treatments.\n\n3. **Tranquil Touch Spa**:\n   - **Location**: 8200 Humboldt Ave S, Bloomington, MN 55431 (just outside Minneapolis)\n   - **Description**: Tranquil Touch Spa provides a range of services including Korean body scrubs and massages. It's praised for its clean facilities and friendly staff, making it a great choice for those seeking a traditional Korean spa experience.\n\nThese spas offer a variety of services and experiences that you might find in a traditional Korean spa, such as saunas, body scrubs, and massages. Enjoy your visit!",
